Godwin ISENYO Operatives of the Kaduna State Police Command on Saturday, confirmed the abduction of five persons by unidentified gunmen at Danbushiya Village in Malali, Kaduna North Area of the state. It was learnt that the gunmen in military fatigue blocked the access road to the Babatunde Fasjola Housing Estate and intercepted a Honda Accord Reg. No. LND 753 AL and five  (5) other vehicles where they  kidnapped seven persons. Spokesman of the command, DSP Yakubu Sabo, however, said after  much pressure following the general patrol of the area  by crack team of the police, two persons were released by the suspected kidnappers. He also said upon search, $10,000 US Dollars and N647,300 were recovered from one of the vehicles. The spokesman added that the combined team of the command’s anti-kidnap squad and vigilante have been dispatched to scene for search operation with the view to apprehending the perpetrators. Copyright PUNCH.
